name: Kashi Dairy veg restaurant

reviews.review_text:
Location is good - at a walkable distance both from Vasco Bus Stand and Vasco Railway Station.
The food is strictly veg and tastes excellent. Comparing the quantity and quality with other available options nearby, this restaurant is far better than anyone.
Behaviour of the staffs are excellent and response is also professional. The pricing of food is also very much affordable.
The only factor I've observed is it's seating capacity is not sufficient according to demand and number of customers incoming. Thus, always a waiting crowd may be seen during the peak hours.
Apart from this, like more other restaurants nearby, this place doesn't have any designated parking place available. The vehicles are to be parked on street on owner's own risk.
But, if you crave for some veg delicacies under pocket friendly budget, I would definitely recommend this place to visit once.

So a friend of mine randomly remembered this place where he had eaten this AMAZING paratha in 2008. Didn't remember anything but the taste of the paratha from back then. We googled the best paratha in Vasco, and this was one of the first places. We saw the photos and narrowed them down because this looked the best.

When my friend had the first bite, he knew this was the place we were looking for! Such is the taste of this place that everyone remembered it after 15-odd years!

The place is generally open very late, till 11 o'clock. There are two sittings, one non-ac on the ground floor and AC on the first floor.
They have takeaways as well, which probably comprise most of their orders. This can mean the service is slow, but that's not the case here. The staff is active, and the small kitchen on the first floor makes getting smaller things out quickly possible. But but, we've seen the waiter get lost and forget which table ordered the fried rice. So that was a meh.

We ordered the classic Aloo Paratha, which they serve hot with curd. We also ordered Matar Paneer because it was too late to eat curd. The paratha was stuffed and was more than enough for one person's meal. The matar paneer tasted really good as well.
Not sure if the AC/non-AC sitting has different prices, but the price was really affordable for the taste and the service in the AC section as well.

Overall, it was a great experience, mainly because of the story my friend had with the place. But kudos to the restaurant for not disappointing!
Would definitely recommend it for lunch/dinner if you like parathas.

Good food, chole bhature, samosa is the best small in size though as compare to price,
Chole bhature is an excellent choice and so does the pav bhaji
I will never prefer to order aloo Paratha here. Was not as per my expectations.
Lassi is must try..
Massala Dosa is ok, but not as per mark..

description:
**Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant: A Veggie Delight in the Heart of Goa**

Tucked into the vibrant locale of Vasco, Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant stands out with a commendable overall rating of 3.8, reflecting the experiences of over 926 enthusiastic patrons. Priding itself on a strictly vegetarian menu, the restaurant has gained a following for its rich offering of comfort food, including *aloo paratha* and *lassi*, which both received 21 mentions each, along with beloved *samosas*, highlighted 18 times in customer reviews. Those seeking hearty, wallet-friendly vegetarian options will find Kashi Dairy to be a satisfying pit stop.

**Ambiance & Design**

Walking into Kashi Dairy is like stepping into a cozy, family-friendly space where bright colors and simple furnishings immediately create an inviting atmosphere. The non-air-conditioned area on the ground floor and the cooler, air-conditioned first floor provide patrons with options based on preference and comfort. Reviewers have noted that while the seating capacity often feels limited, likely due to its popularity during peak hours, the restaurant maintains a warm and bustling vibe, accompanied by soft music that enhances the dining experience. A common theme echoed by visitors is the lack of designated parking, prompting most to park on the roadside, which adds a slight sense of adventure to a lunch or dinner outing.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Kashi Dairy's menu is a treasure chest of vegetarian delights, with signature dishes that have been etched in the memories of locals for years. The *aloo paratha*, often served steaming hot with a side of creamy curd, is a long-standing favorite that not only lives up to its reputation but has also earned a loyal fan base over the years. Customers cherish the generous stuffing and the comforting ambiance while savoring their meals, as seen in delightful photos showcasing both the beautifully plated dishes and the inviting dining space.

Reviewers have praised the *chole bhature* and *pav bhaji*, both hailed as must-tries. However, the *massala dosa* received mixed reviews, suggesting that while some items shine extraordinarily, others may not hit the mark for every palate. Additionally, the *lassi* stands as a highlight, consistently recommended as an accompaniment to an already rich meal. Dietary preferences are well accommodated, with a substantial vegetarian menu that includes gluten-free and dairy options.

**Customer Experience & Service**

The service at Kashi Dairy is often lauded, with numerous reviewers complimenting the staff's professionalism and friendliness. While the bustling nature of the restaurant sometimes leads to a slower experience—especially during busy hours or with takeaway orders—the efficiency of the staff generally keeps the experience smooth and enjoyable. One notable insight from a review shared the occasional mix-up with orders, suggesting that further training could benefit staff in high-volume scenarios. However, diners frequently report that their tables are greeted promptly and that overall service remains attentive.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Kashi Dairy has carved out a reputation not just through word-of-mouth, but through its standing in social and food circles. As diners revisit fond memories tied to their meals here, the restaurant's nostalgic quality has made it a beloved gem for both locals and tourists alike. Critics and foodies alike appreciate the balance of quality and affordability, with offerings priced to attract a diverse crowd.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The visual allure of Kashi Dairy is palpable through customer-shared photos, each capturing the essence of what this restaurant represents: hearty servings and cheerful dining experiences. The fun, vibrant hues of the walls accentuate the warmth, while close-ups of the *aloo paratha* and other favorites showcase the attention to detail in food presentation.

In conclusion, Kashi Dairy Veg Restaurant is more than just an eatery; it serves as a community gathering point for those seeking delicious vegetarian dishes in Goa. With its welcoming atmosphere, stellar *aloo parathas*, and attentive service, it invites diners to stop by and create their own memories in a setting that celebrates the joy of vegetarian cooking and camaraderie.
